# How to collect data in Lytics

Lytics can collect data from various sources to build comprehensive user profiles. Here's how to implement data collection:

1. Choose your data collection method based on your needs:
   - Website tracking (JavaScript tag)
   - Mobile app tracking (iOS/Android SDKs)
   - Server-side API
   - Batch imports
   - Third-party integrations

2. For website tracking:
   - Add the Lytics JavaScript tag to your site
   - Install the tag in the `<head>` section of your pages
   - Configure default settings in the tag
   - Set up custom event tracking

3. Basic JavaScript implementation:

```javascript
// Basic Lytics tag installation
<script>
(function(l,y,t,i,c,s) {
    l['LyticsObjectTracker']=i;
    l[i]=l[i]||function(){(l[i].q=l[i].q||[]).push(arguments)},l[i].v=1,l[i].l=1*new Date();
    c=y.createElement(t),s=y.getElementsByTagName(t)[0];c.async=1;c.src='//c.lytics.io/static/io.min.js';
    s.parentNode.insertBefore(c,s);
})(window,document,'script','jstag');

// Initialize with your account ID
jstag('config', 'YOUR_ACCOUNT_ID_HERE');
</script>
```

4. Track user events:

```javascript
// Track a page view
jstag('send', 'pageview');

// Track a custom event
jstag('send', 'event', {
  event_name: 'button_click',
  category: 'engagement',
  label: 'signup_button'
});
```

5. For server-side collection, use the REST API:
   - Obtain your API token
   - Send events using HTTP requests
   - Use batch endpoints for multiple events

6. For third-party platforms:
   - Navigate to Integrations in the Lytics dashboard
   - Set up the connection to your existing tools
   - Configure data mapping and sync settings

After implementation, data will flow into Lytics and begin building user profiles automatically.
